Kamala Harris eyes Joe Rogan podcast to win over young male voters
item.description: Democratic nominee Kamala Harris is considering an interview with Joe Rogan to gain support among young male voters. Rogan's podcast reaches millions and could be influential. Harris' campaign also targeted Black male voters and confirmed an interview with Fox News. Trump plans a Rogan appearance too, adding tension to the tight race.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: What is Shaken Baby Syndrome, that might lead to Texas man's execution over daughter's death?
item.description: Robert Roberson, 57, is set to be executed in Texas for a murder conviction related to shaken baby syndrome. His lawyers, alongside experts, claim that the conviction was based on faulty evidence and undiagnosed medical issues. Despite new evidence, courts have denied appeals, raising concerns about the diagnosis' role in forensic science.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Over 200 pro-Palestinian supporters arrested outside NY Stock Exchange
item.description: Police arrested over 200 pro-Palestinian protestors outside the New York Stock Exchange, demanding an end to US support for Israel's military actions in Gaza. Protesters, organized by various activist groups, chanted slogans against US defense contractors and raised concerns over alleged genocide. A smaller group of pro-Israel supporters also gathered at the site.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Harry and Meghan 'trial separation': Prince reportedly leading separate life from 'control freak' Markle
item.description: Prince Harry and Meghan Markle are reportedly drifting apart with Harry leading solo outings and embracing a different energy. Harry seems to rediscover his happiness away from Meghan, causing speculation about a trial separation as they navigate their individual desires and futures amidst challenges in their marriage and professional lives.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Washington's National Zoo welcomes two giant Pandas from China
item.description: The Smithsonian's National Zoo in Washington, DC, is set to welcome two energetic giant pandas, Bao Li and Qing Bao, from China. Born in 2021, they start a new chapter in panda conservation efforts. This arrival coincides with heightened U.S.-China diplomatic ties and is part of a broader initiative to protect the vulnerable species.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 2,000-year-old tomb with 12 skeletons discovered in Jordan
item.description: Archaeologists uncover a 2,000-year-old tomb beneath Petra's Treasury in Jordan, revealing 12 skeletons and well-preserved artifacts. Led by Dr. Pearce Paul Creasman, the team explores the significance of the burial site and its insights into Nabataean culture and history.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Record 153 Chinese military aircraft fly around Taiwan airspace
item.description: Taiwan detected 153 Chinese military aircraft around its airspace in a single day, setting a record. The maneuvers occurred amid high tensions and followed China's large-scale military drills. Taiwan and the U.S. condemned the actions, while Japan expressed concerns. Taiwan's President vowed to protect the island's democracy and sovereignty.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: North Korea blows up inter-Korean roads amid rising tensions with South
item.description: North Korea has dismantled sections of inter-Korean roads on its side of the border, signaling a further deterioration in inter-Korean relations. This move, along with accusations against South Korea of flying drones over Pyongyang, heightens tensions and prompts military readiness between the two nations.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Canadian Sikhs stalked by fear,' claims NDP's Jagmeet Singh, calls for sanctions against India
item.description: Amidst tensions between India and Canada over the murder of Hardeep Singh Nijjar, New Democratic Party (NDP) leader Jagmeet Singh urged the Canadian government to take action against India, specifically calling for diplomat sanctions and a ban on the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh (RSS) Network in Canada.

item.title: Nasa launches Europa Clipper to explore potential life on Jupiter's moon
item.description: Nasa launched the Europa Clipper spacecraft to explore Jupiter's moon Europa, aiming to investigate its subsurface ocean for habitability. The mission, costing $5.2 billion, features nine instruments to study Europa's environment, expecting to reach Jupiter by 2030, and conduct 49 flybys over four years.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Kamala shares montage of Trump at Pennsylvania rally, slams 'enemy from within' remark
item.description: US Vice President Kamala Harris criticizes Donald Trump in a Pennsylvania rally, warning against his potential re-election. She shares a montage of Trump's speeches discussing the threats posed by 'enemies within' and his willingness to use military force against them, targeting journalists and election officials.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Diddy's infamous 'White Parties' were hotbeds for sexual assault: New lawsuits
item.description: Sean 'Diddy' Combs faces new sexual assault allegations linked to various incidents at his 'White Parties', a Manhattan hotel, and a Macy's stockroom. Attorney Tony Buzbee represents six unidentified victims and plans more lawsuits. Diddy is currently in detention, awaiting trial in 2025 on multiple charges, including racketeering and sex trafficking.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Facebook and Instagram outages impact thousands in US
item.description: Meta platforms' Facebook and Instagram faced significant outages across the US on Monday, with users reporting over 8,000 issues for Facebook and 4,000 for Instagram around 1:44 pm ET. Most services were restored by 2:09 pm ET. Earlier this year, a global Meta outage affected hundreds of thousands of users for over two hours.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: King Charles pauses cancer treatment for Australian tour
item.description: King Charles temporarily pauses cancer treatment for an 11-day tour of Australia with Queen Camilla, as doctors clear him with a reduced schedule. The visit aims to strengthen ties amidst rising republican sentiments. Meanwhile, Prince William and Princess Kate increasingly step up, raising speculation about a power shift within the royal family.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Kamala Harris' policy list: 'Opportunity Agenda for Black Men' to win voters. Details here.
item.description: Kamala Harris revealed an economic initiative, the 'Opportunity Agenda for Black men,' targeting Black business owners with forgivable loans and national marijuana legalization for economic inclusion. Aiming to regain Black male support before the November election, her agenda also covers cryptocurrency regulations, educational opportunities, and a health equity initiative.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Honestly kind of shocking': GOP leader Anna Paulina Luna surprised by Biden's Hurricane response
item.description: Republican Anna Paulina Luna praised President Biden for his proactive response to Hurricane Milton's impact on her Florida district. Despite her past criticisms, Luna appreciated Biden's efforts in disaster aid reforms and FEMA's performance, advocating for changes to improve federal disaster response.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: JD Vance slams Kamala Harris for allegedly using Wikipedia to write her book
item.description: US vice president Kamala Harris is accused of plagiarism in her 2009 book 'Smart on Crime,' allegedly copying sections from uncited sources, including Wikipedia and news reports. Conservative writer Christopher Rufo and Austrian plagiarism expert Stefan Weber highlight over a dozen instances, raising concerns about the integrity of Harris's work. Senator JD Vance also criticized Harris publicly.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Kamala Harris will give an interview to not-so-friendly Fox News. Details here
item.description: Kamala Harris Fox interview: The interview will take place near Philadelphia on Wednesday shortly before it gets aired at 6 PM Eastern Time at Bret Baier's "Special Report". The vice president will sit for 25 to 30 minutes. Bret Baier is the chief political anchor at the network. This will be Kamala Harris's first formal interview with Fox News.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Lilly Ledbetter, activist behind landmark equal pay law, dies at 86: Obama pays tribute
item.description: Lilly Ledbetter, renowned for her equal pay activism, passed away at 86. Her work led to the Lilly Ledbetter Fair Pay Restoration Act, signed by President Obama in 2009. She recently received the Future Is Female Lifetime Achievement Award, and her life story inspired the film 'Lilly'.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
